---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import SiteFooter from "../components/SiteFooter.astro";
import { CONTACT_EMAIL } from "../data/site";

const lastUpdated = "21 June 2026";
---

<Layout
  title="Privacy policy | Screwdriver Marketing"
  description="How Screwdriver Marketing collects, uses, and protects personal information when you visit our website or get in touch."
>
  <div class="relative min-h-screen overflow-x-hidden">
    <header class="relative z-10 border-b border-[var(--border)] bg-bg-deep/80 backdrop-blur-md">
      <div class="mx-auto flex max-w-3xl items-center justify-between gap-4 px-5 py-4 sm:px-6">
        <a href="/" class="group flex items-center gap-2">
          <span
            class="font-display flex h-10 w-10 items-center justify-center rounded-xl bg-gradient-to-br from-accent to-accent-glow text-lg font-extrabold text-bg-deep shadow-lg shadow-accent/20 transition group-hover:scale-105"
            aria-hidden="true">S</span
          >
          <span class="font-display text-lg font-bold tracking-tight sm:text-xl">
            Screwdriver <span class="text-accent">Marketing</span>
          </span>
        </a>
        <a href="/" class="text-sm font-medium text-muted transition hover:text-cream">← Back to home</a>
      </div>
    </header>

    <main class="relative z-10 px-5 py-16 sm:px-6 sm:py-20">
      <article class="legal-prose mx-auto max-w-3xl">
        <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest text-accent">Legal</p>
        <h1 class="font-display mt-2 text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight sm:text-4xl">Privacy policy</h1>
        <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-muted">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>

        <p class="mt-8 text-muted leading-relaxed">
          Screwdriver Marketing (<strong class="font-medium text-cream">we</strong>, <strong class="font-medium text-cream">us</strong>, or <strong class="font-medium text-cream">our</strong>) respects your privacy. This policy explains how we handle personal information when you visit screwdrivermarketing.com.au (or related pages we operate), contact us, or use our services.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-4 text-sm text-muted leading-relaxed">
          This policy is general information only. It is not legal advice. If you need advice about your specific situation, speak to a qualified professional.
        </p>

        <h2>Who we are</h2>
        <p>
          Screwdriver Marketing provides websites, SEO, Google Business Profile support, lead tracking, and related digital marketing services for local service businesses in Adelaide and across Australia.
        </p>
        <p>
          Privacy enquiries: <a href={`mailto:${CONTACT_EMAIL}`}>{CONTACT_EMAIL}</a>
        </p>

        <h2>What information we collect</h2>
        <p>Depending on how you interact with us, we may collect:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong class="text-cream">Contact details</strong> — such as your name, business name, email address, phone number, and website URL when you request a strategy call, submit our website audit form, or email us directly.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong class="text-cream">Message content</strong> — what you tell us about your business, goals, or support needs.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong class="text-cream">Usage and technical data</strong> — such as pages viewed, links clicked, browser type, device type, and approximate location (e.g. city or region from IP address). We may collect this through analytics or event tracking on our site.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong class="text-cream">Client project information</strong> — if you become a client, we may handle business information you provide for your website, Google Business Profile, or marketing (including access credentials you choose to share). We treat client data separately under our service agreement with you.
          </li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          We do not intentionally collect sensitive information (such as health records or government identifiers) through this marketing website. Please do not send that information unless we have agreed it is necessary for a specific service.
        </p>

        <h2>How we collect information</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Directly from you — forms, email, phone, or messages.</li>
          <li>Automatically — cookies, pixels, or similar technologies if we use analytics or advertising tools.</li>
          <li>From third parties — for example, referral partners or publicly available business listings, where relevant to a project.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>How we use your information</h2>
        <p>We use personal information to:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Respond to enquiries and provide quotes, audits, or strategy calls.</li>
          <li>Deliver and improve our services for clients.</li>
          <li>Understand how visitors use our website so we can improve content and conversion paths.</li>
          <li>Send service-related messages (for example, replies to your enquiry or project updates).</li>
          <li>Meet legal, accounting, or regulatory obligations.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          We do not sell your personal information. We may send occasional marketing about our services where permitted by law. You can opt out of marketing emails at any time by replying or using an unsubscribe link if provided.
        </p>

        <h2>Website audit form and email</h2>
        <p>
          Our audit request form prepares an email to us with the details you enter. Submitting the form opens your email app; we receive your information when you send that email. Please only include information you are comfortable sharing.
        </p>

        <h2>Tracking and analytics</h2>
        <p>
          We may record interactions on this site (for example, button clicks, form submissions, or phone/email link taps) to understand what helps visitors get in touch. This may use first-party scripts or third-party analytics services. Where we use third-party tools, those providers may process data according to their own policies.
        </p>

        <h2>Cookies</h2>
        <p>
          Cookies are small files stored on your device. We may use essential cookies for basic site function and optional cookies for analytics or performance measurement. You can control cookies through your browser settings. Blocking cookies may affect how some parts of the site work.
        </p>

        <h2>Who we share information with</h2>
        <p>We may share personal information with:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Service providers who help us operate (hosting, email, analytics, project tools) — only as needed and under appropriate confidentiality expectations.</li>
          <li>Professional advisers (accountants, lawyers) when required.</li>
          <li>Authorities if required by law or to protect our rights, safety, or the rights of others.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          Some providers may store or process data outside Australia. Where that occurs, we take reasonable steps to ensure appropriate handling consistent with applicable privacy law.
        </p>

        <h2>How we protect information</h2>
        <p>
          We use reasonable technical and organisational measures to protect personal information from misuse, loss, unauthorised access, modification, or disclosure. No online transmission or storage is completely secure; we cannot guarantee absolute security.
        </p>

        <h2>How long we keep information</h2>
        <p>
          We keep information only as long as needed for the purposes above, including to respond to enquiries, deliver services, resolve disputes, and meet legal record-keeping requirements. When information is no longer needed, we take reasonable steps to delete or de-identify it.
        </p>

        <h2>Your rights</h2>
        <p>
          Under the Australian Privacy Act 1988 and the Australian Privacy Principles (APPs), you may have the right to:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Ask whether we hold personal information about you and request access.</li>
          <li>Request correction of inaccurate, out-of-date, incomplete, or misleading information.</li>
          <li>Make a complaint about how we handle your information.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          To exercise these rights, contact us at <a href={`mailto:${CONTACT_EMAIL}`}>{CONTACT_EMAIL}</a>. We will respond within a reasonable time. If you are not satisfied with our response, you may contact the Office of the Australian Information Commissioner (OAIC) at <a href="https://www.oaic.gov.au/" rel="noopener noreferrer">oaic.gov.au</a>.
        </p>

        <h2>Links to other websites</h2>
        <p>
          Our site may link to third-party websites (for example, Google Maps or social platforms). We are not responsible for their privacy practices. Review their policies before providing personal information.
        </p>

        <h2>Children</h2>
        <p>
          Our services are aimed at businesses. This site is not directed at children under 18, and we do not knowingly collect their personal information.
        </p>

        <h2>Changes to this policy</h2>
        <p>
          We may update this policy from time to time. The &ldquo;Last updated&rdquo; date at the top will change when we do. Continued use of the site after changes means you accept the updated policy.
        </p>

        <h2>Contact us</h2>
        <p>
          Questions about this privacy policy or how we handle your information:
        </p>
        <p>
          <strong class="text-cream">Screwdriver Marketing</strong><br />
          Email: <a href={`mailto:${CONTACT_EMAIL}`}>{CONTACT_EMAIL}</a><br />
          Adelaide, South Australia, Australia
        </p>
      </article>
    </main>

    <SiteFooter />
  </div>
</Layout>

<style>
  .legal-prose h2 {
    margin-top: 2.5rem;
    font-family: var(--font-syne);
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--cream);
  }

  .legal-prose p {
    margin-top: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: var(--muted);
  }

  .legal-prose ul {
    margin-top: 1rem;
    list-style: disc;
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
    color: var(--muted);
  }

  .legal-prose li {
    margin-top: 0.5rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .legal-prose a {
    color: var(--signal);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 2px;
  }

  .legal-prose a:hover {
    color: var(--cream);
  }
</style>
